<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-219-586  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 219 586.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MIS Week  March 5 1990 v11 n10 p34(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Decentralized, international team key to global MIS strategy.andO;(multinational companies)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Dymond, Rebecca.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Careful strategic planning is necessary for effective MIS inmultinational corporations.andP;  A decentralized team composed ofstaff members from each nation in which the company operates isthe most effective method, according to experts.andP;  Dow Chemical Couses a steering committee composed of representatives from eachgeographically dispersed business unit, while Salomon Brothers Incuses an international team for system development and design.andO;Different locations have different cultures, and managers try toavoid imposing a central style on the teams.andP;  Teleconferencinghelps international MIS teams coordinate reports.andP;  Human resourcedevelopment is especially important in sustaining a globalstrategy.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Multinational CorporationMISStrategic PlanningManagement of EDPDecentralizationTeam Approach.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>